HEADWORD: Phosphate
<hw>Phos"phate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A salt of phosphoric acid or a compound containing the phosphate
radical group <chform>-PO4</chform>; <as>as, trisodium phosphate
(<chform>Na3PO4</chform>); triethyl phosphate
(<chform>(C2H5)3PO4</chform>)</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phosphatic</ent>⟦br⟧
